main event: Two civilian witnesses sighted a cigar or diamond-shaped object in Duluth, Minnesota, on 21 October 1952.
interesting points: Witnesses described the object as having a size of approximately 51' x 51' x 9',The object moved slowly close to the ground before ascending rapidly,The object seemed to leave a faint bluish glow trail,One witness claimed the object traveled at speeds up to 300 mph,The object was reportedly able to throw stones.
